    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>The default scope is package-private. All classes in the same package can access the method/field/class. Package-private is stricter than protected and public scopes, but more permissive than private scope.</p>\n\n<p>More information:<br>\n<a href=\"http://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/java/javaOO/accesscontrol.html\" rel=\"noreferrer\">http://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/java/javaOO/accesscontrol.html</a><br>\n<a href=\"http://mindprod.com/jgloss/scope.html\" rel=\"noreferrer\">http://mindprod.com/jgloss/scope.html</a></p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 8476,
      "reputation" : 380,
      "user_id" : 15299,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/dffe466bbed30ed4aa9fad9d77d191ea?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "user15299",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/15299/user15299"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 20,
    "last_activity_date" : 1238778281,
    "creation_date" : 1238778281,
    "answer_id" : 714832,
    "question_id" : 714791,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 2.5",
    "body" : "<p>Anything defined as package private can be accessed by the class itself, other classes within the same package, but not outside of the package, and not by sub-classes.</p>\n\n<p>See <a href=\"http://java.sun.com/docs/books/tutorial/java/javaOO/accesscontrol.html\" rel=\"noreferrer\">this page</a> for a handy table of access level modifiers...</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 2496,
      "reputation" : 270515,
      "user_id" : 3474,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 83,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/ffbf4e85b8ffbae4e9039b9c0cf07bc8?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "erickson",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/3474/erickson"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 9,
    "last_activity_date" : 1238779107,
    "creation_date" : 1238779107,
    "answer_id" : 714874,
    "question_id" : 714791,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 2.5",
    "body" : "<p>Without an access modifier, a class member is accessible throughout the package in which it's declared. You can learn more from the <a href=\"http://java.sun.com/docs/books/jls/third_edition/html/names.html#6.6\" rel=\"noreferrer\">Java Language Specification, §6.6.</a></p>\n\n<p>Members of an interface are always publicly accessible, whether explicitly declared or not.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "user_type" : "does_not_exist",
      "display_name" : "user1011455"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1336564977,
    "creation_date" : 1336564977,
    "answer_id" : 10515684,
    "question_id" : 714791,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>If you are not giving any modifier to your method then as default it will be Default modifier which has scope within package.<br>\nfor more info you can refer <a href=\"http://wiki.answers.com/Q/What_is_default_access_specifier_in_Java\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://wiki.answers.com/Q/What_is_default_access_specifier_in_Java</a></p>\n"
  }, {
